Definition: You've been given a list of numbers, and your output must be a list of the averages of all successive values.

Positive Examples.explanation: This is a good example. The output is a list of averages of the two consecutive values in the list
The list of the list is a single value, because the input has only two elements and thus the average of those two would give us the output

Negative Examples.explanation: The output has computed only for the first few elements in the list, so this is a bad example
This output is the output of the entire list, but not the average of the consecutive two values, so it's wrong
